Package: distrib
Title: S3 Framework for Probability Distributions
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Giovanni", "Tinervia", , "giovannitinervia9@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a consistent S3 object-oriented infrastructure for probability distributions. Each 'distrib' object encapsulates standard statistical functions (PDF, CDF, Quantile) alongside analytical gradients, Hessians, and link functions. The package includes robust validation tools to verify analytical derivatives against numerical approximations.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
URL: https://github.com/giovannitinervia9/distrib
BugReports: https://github.com/giovannitinervia9/distrib/issues
Depends: 
    linkfunctions (>= 0.0.0.9000)
Remotes: 
    giovannitinervia9/linkfunctions
Imports: 
    numDeriv,
    purrr,
    statmod
